content.description: Climb the reverse steps without using the left arete or the Danger City crack. (Yellow route line in photo).
content.location: Far left wall of Galt Line boudler

content.description: Middle Route on binary wall. Find obvious pinch and move up center face. Slab climbing over mossy feet. Right Arete and left crack off for full effect.
content.location: Binary wall. Behind and to the left of Tree people boulder.

content.description: Head up the chimney underneath the large tree, topping out left of the tree. "A" in photo.
content.location: Tree People Boulder

content.description: Start matched on the slopey arete around chest height. Climb up the arete and top out.  Crux is the beginning.
content.location: Far right on the Tree People Boulder

content.description: on Arête right of Tacos for Dinner.  Climb straight up the Arête. HIGHBALL
content.location: Found on Galt Line Boulder on fisherman's trail

content.description:
SDS on left side of overhang, right on a crimp underneath the overhang and left on sloppey jug. Crimp broke recently, Start matched on sloppey jug and work your way up the arête and top out. 

youtube.com/watch?v=ARYnH5f…
content.location: On Shark Tooth Boulder on Fisherman's Trail

content.description: Start on left facing flake/crack in about middle of formation.  Work your way up the flake.
content.location: Found on Galt Line Boulder on Fisherman's Trail

content.description: Head up the slabby corner to the left of "Tacos for Dinner." Be cautious of loose, flaky rock on the overhang.
content.location: Galt Line Boulder

content.description: SDS on the right side of the overhang, move out from under the overhang to the right , then go straight up to a top out.
content.location: On the Shark Tooth Boulder on Fisherman's trail

content.description: Follow crack up into a high section of offwidth. Top out on left side of offwidth. HIGHBALL. (Blue route line in photo provided).
content.location: Galt Line Boulder

content.description: Climb straight up the slab to the right of Not a Bad Little Crack for a Chick
content.location: Tree People Boulder

content.description:
Right side of the Tooth boulder (to the right of "Straight Up").  Starts sitting, matched in a low undercling, climb straight up the face to a bigger edge then easy top out. 

  I am not sure if this is a first ascent - I thought it might be since the obvious starting footholds were exfoliating.  If someone else has done this already please let me know and I will update the information.
content.location: Right side of Tooth boulder.

content.description: Follow Flea Collar up, cutting left at the gap and continuing through the two upper walls. (Blue in photo)

Start matched in the crack of the left Arête at about chest height, move up and left to the slopey jug, move up to a solid pinch then out onto the slopey rail to the top out.

youtube.com/watch?v=1IQatR_…
content.protection: 3 pads at least and 2 spotters recommended. Pads need to be moved right a little when climber moves onto the slopey rail.
content.location: Found on Porteños Formation on the Fisherman's Trail

content.description: Start low right on obvious rail, throw to the lip to find a good jug, mantel up over the lip and top out to the left.
content.location: On Double Helix Fibers Boulder on Fisherman's trail

content.description: SDS, Stretch wide to starting (opposing) side-pulls with delicate feet, pull off the ground, then dead-point to crimp rail with either hand.  Easy top out after. Kind of a 1-2 move wonder, but it was there and so was I.  I'm sure it's much harder if you have a small ape index/can't reach both start holds and have to use only one...
content.protection: maybe a pad, but not crucial
content.location: Right side of Shark Tooth Boulder, Fisherman's Path

climbs.name: Not a Bad Little Crack for a Chick

content.description: Follow the crack just to the right of the main chimney. Route "B" in the photo.
content.location: Tree People Boulder

content.description: Follow Doggy Bag up to the large gap, continuing through the gap and straight up to top out. Be mindful of loose flakes. (Green line in photo).
content.location: Doggy Bag Boulder

content.description: Hop on the mossy face and move up up to the excellent pocket. Move to the arete and follow it to the top. once past the tree its a sketchy fall
content.location: to the left and up of the tree people boulder

content.description: On the right side of cave, start matched at bottom of right facing  crack, climb up the crack to a good pinch at the arête, then move onto the face, and top out.
content.protection: Pad and Spotter, some rocks hidden under all the leaves
content.location: On Recessed Cave Formation on Fisherman's Trail

content.description: In between "Tighten Up (V4) and Straight Up (V2). Right hand on the undercling low in the roof. Left hand on a jug of Tighten up. Climb the roof problem. The problem has unique hand holds that you won't find outdoors in Maryland (bomber pinches).
content.location: Inbetween "Tighten Up (V4) and Straight Up (V2) at Shark Tooth Boulder.

content.description:
Starting just below the underling for "Klingon" with left in the crack and right underneath the boulder, rock low to your right is on for a foot if needed, from start move into undercling of "Klingon" and finish out the same. Big power needed to move into the undercling. 

youtube.com/watch?v=2805g1x…
content.location: on Recessed Cave Formation on Fisherman's trail

content.description: On the left side of the cave, start matched on an undercling, move out left to crack/flake, work up the crack/flake and find a good jug, pull up onto the stream facing face and top out.
content.location: On Recessed Cave Formation on Fisherman's trail

content.description: Climb slightly overhung jugs to the left of Aloha
content.location: Jugs up the face left of Aloha

content.description:
Start matched on good slopers in the back left corner.  Work across the roof on good holds toward the right side of the boulder, hold the swing and top out just around the corner. 

youtube.com/watch?v=6A3dKvr…
content.protection: Will need a few pads and a spotter to keep you out of the stream if you bow the top out.  Not very tall but rocky landing sloping into the stream
content.location: Found on the Stones Throw boulder on the fisherman's path.  From the Crumb boulders this boulder is found back upstream just a little ways across the stream.  Best time to go here is probably when it is a little warmer since you will need to wade across.  Don't worry it is only about shin height if you cross at the right point.

content.description: Found on Right Arête, Start on crimps and work up to a top out
content.protection: Pad or 2, Gets a little tall
content.location: Found on Porteños Formation on Fisherman's trail

content.description:
Start in the back left corner of the boulder matched on a good sloper rail.  Worker the sloper rail out to the face of the boulder with good heel hooks and make a move up and top out. 

youtube.com/watch?v=C9GMsws…
content.protection: few pads and a spotter to keep you out of the stream
content.location: Found on the Stones Throw boulder on the fisherman's path. From the Crumb boulders this boulder is found back upstream just a little ways across the stream. Best time to go here is probably when it is a little warmer since you will need to wade across. Don't worry it is only about shin height if you cross at the right point.

content.description: Fun little route on an interesting feature, slightly awkward face movement into a big reach around to top out. Arete and top left ledge are off. Start sitting low on a dish out left and a sidepull right, move up the face on sidepulls and a gaston until moving right to the big jug under the overhang. From here, reach around to a good hold on the front face of the mallet and slap your way up the left face until you reach a good jug at the top, then top out left.
content.location: On the Mallet boulder near the end of fisherman's trail, obvious formation with a smaller boulder leaning off the edge of another.

content.description: Found about the middle of the face, Start on a left facing side pull and horizontal rail at about head height and move straight up the face.
content.protection: Pad or 2, gets a little tall
content.location: Found on Porteños Formation on the Fisherman's Trail

content.description: Start underneath boulder, left on sloper right on decent crimp, move out to the rail and finish like "Over the Top."
content.location: On Double Helix Fibers Boulder on Fisherman's Trail

content.description: Follow good holds along the crack up to a crux high foot to top out.  HIGHBALL. (Green route line in picture provided).
content.location: Found on Galt Line Boulder. Follows the crack to the right of Spaceballs.

content.description: Start from good holds on the right side of the main face. Head up and to the right at the large gap. (Red line in photo).
content.location: Doggy Bag Boulder

content.description:
Start underneath boulder, left on sloper right on decent crimp, just like "From Down Unda", move out to the rail and traverse the rail left, then top out straight up.     Rocks the boulder is leaning on are off 

youtube.com/watch?v=S8aFmtf…
content.location: On Double Helix Fibers Boulder on Fisherman's trail

content.description: Found on the far right end of the Galt Line formation. Start on right hand jug and left undercling on the horizontal scar, heading straight up to the top.
content.location: Galt Line boulder

content.description: Start on the left side of the face, going up and toping out left at the large gap. (Yellow in photo)
content.location: Left side of Doggy Bag boulder

content.description: Wide crack to the right of Dreams of Babylon. (Red route in photo provided).
content.location: Galt Line Boulder

content.description: Start low right on obvious rail, same as "Over the Top", traverse the rail left, then top out straight up.     Rocks the boulder is leaning on are off.
content.location: On Double Helix Fibers Boulder on Fisherman's trail

content.description: Start deep in the cave, find good holds in the crack, work your way up the crack, find a sharp crimp on the right wall and move out to the face and establish and exit left or top out.
content.location: On Recessed Cave Formation on Fisherman's Trail

content.description:
Previously known as "Tons of Friends" project but was found to be sent by Justin Ridgely years ago. Start on underclings down low. Move up the overhanging face through crimps to jugs at the lip. 

youtu.be/NFhO5wIPwGI
content.location: Left side of the Porteños boulder

content.description: Far right slab of the Tree People boulder. Climb between the right-most crack on the boulder and the right hand arete. Mind the awkward top out.
content.location: Tree People Boulder

content.description:
It has come to my attention that the majority of the climbing located on Fisherman's could be located on  PRIVATE PROPERTY .    Until this gets figured out please : 

Keep groups smallNo music No yelling, even when you send your projectDo not hike up above the boulders If confronted by someone saying they are a landowner please stay polite and leave and let contact me at morganrunguide@gmail.com

  Found on the opposite side of the road from the parking lot.  Has a lot of tall formations with highball potential or could be top roped.
